OL,7,F"Nobody's free, I'm ill, the wife's
OL,8,Fill..." she said. "It was just one
OL,9,Fthing after another to begin with, we
OL,10,Fkind of gave him the benefit of the
OL,11,Fdoubt."
OL,13,FFor months, Jane said almost nothing
OL,14,Fwas done, and then she realised she
OL,15,Fwas being fooled.
OL,17,F"It was like an epiphany, it's the
OL,18,Fonly way I can describe it.
OL,20,F"He'd been stringing us along the
OL,21,Fwhole time," she said.
