OL,7,FSharland's two-year prison sentence
OL,8,Fwas suspended for two years and he was
OL,9,Fgiven 220 hours of community service
OL,10,Fas well as 15 days of rehabilitation.
OL,12,FHe was also disqualified from being a
OL,13,Fdirector of a company for seven years.
OL,15,FHis honour Judge Taylor told Sharland
OL,16,Fthat his conduct had been "a
OL,17,Fnightmare" for the householders
OL,18,Faffected and that the work was done so
OL,19,Fpoorly "substantial amounts (of money)
OL,20,Fwere needed to rectify this work".
